# Strategic AI Ethics & Governance Roadmap

## Phase 1: Core Cybersecurity + AI Literacy (Foundation Layer)
**Goal:** Build credibility in security, privacy, and AI fundamentals.

| Certification / Course             | Focus                      | Source                                                                 | Cost     | Time     |
|-----------------------------------|-----------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------|----------|
| Cisco CCST Cybersecurity          | Cybersecurity basics        | https://www.netacad.com/                                               | Free–Low | ~20 hrs  |
| CompTIA Security+                 | Security fundamentals       | https://www.comptia.org/                                               | Med      | ~40–60 hrs|
| Microsoft SC-900                  | Security, compliance, identity| https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/         | Free–Low | ~20 hrs  |
| Google Cybersecurity Certificate | Online safety & privacy     | https://grow.google/intl/ssa-en/courses-and-tools/                     | Free–Low | ~40 hrs  |
| IBM AI Fundamentals               | Intro to AI & ethics        | https://www.ibm.com/training/security                                  | Free     | ~10 hrs  |

---

## Phase 2: AI Ethics, Responsible AI & Governance (Strategic Layer)
**Goal:** Position yourself as a boardroom-ready AI ethics and governance advisor.

| Certification / Course             | Focus                      | Source                                                                 | Cost     | Time     |
|-----------------------------------|-----------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------|----------|
| Microsoft Responsible AI          | Principles & governance     | https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/                            | Free     | ~10–15 hrs|
| Google Responsible AI             | Fairness, bias, transparency| https://grow.google/intl/ssa-en/courses-and-tools/                     | Free     | ~10 hrs  |
| (ISC)² Certified in Cybersecurity | Entry-level GRC             | https://www.isc2.org/                                                  | Free–Low | ~20 hrs  |
| ISACA CISM / CISA                 | Audit, risk, governance     | https://www.isaca.org/                                                 | High     | ~80 hrs  |
| ISECOM OSSTMM / STAR              | Trust & security metrics    | https://www.isecom.org/                                                | Free–Low | ~20 hrs  |

---

## Phase 3: GenAI & GPT Specialization (Operational Layer)
**Goal:** Build hands-on fluency with GenAI tools, risks, and stakeholder applications.

| Certification / Course             | Focus                      | Source                                                                 | Cost     | Time     |
|-----------------------------------|-----------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------|----------|
| Coursera GenAI Specialization     | Prompting, risks, use cases | https://www.coursera.org/                                              | Low–Med  | ~30 hrs  |
| Microsoft Azure AI Engineer (AI-102)| Building AI solutions      | https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/         | Free–Med | ~40–60 hrs|
| Google Cloud GenAI Studio         | GenAI tooling & ethics      | https://console.cloud.google.com/                                     | Free     | ~10–20 hrs|
| GitHub Advanced Security          | Secure AI DevOps            | https://resources.github.com/learn/pathways/security/essentials/      | Free     | ~10 hrs  |
| TryHackMe AI Labs (TBD)           | AI security hands-on        | https://tryhackme.com/welcome                                          | Free–Low | TBD      |

---

## Modular Deployment Strategy

| Track           | Certifications                      | Stakeholder Value                    |
|-----------------|--------------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| Cybersecurity   | CCST, Security+, SC-900              | Privacy, resilience, compliance      |
| Governance      | CISA, CISM, CISSP                    | Risk, audit, boardroom trust         |
| Responsible AI  | Microsoft, Google, IBM               | Ethics, fairness, transparency       |
| GenAI           | AI-102, Coursera, GitHub             | Prompting, tooling, stakeholder fluency|

---

## GitHub-Ready Toolkit Suggestions

- **Ethical AI Glossary** (bias, fairness, explainability)
- **Responsible AI Risk Matrix** (aligned to ISO/IEC 23894)
- **GenAI Prompting Playbook** (for SMEs and boards)
- **Governance Conversation Starters** (GPT-aligned)
